Core monorepo of Pied Piper. Three services in three languages form one data pipeline; every rule in this file is a system-wide contract that each service must honor in its own idiom.

# app Pied Piper Compression Pipeline {#pied_piper_app}

A middle-out compression pipeline composed of three independent processes chained over stdin/stdout:

1. `orchestrator-go` — accepts raw text, wraps it into a traced compression job.
2. `compression-py` — applies the proprietary middle-out algorithm to the job payload.
3. `renderer-ts` — renders the compression result as a human-readable report.

A full run is one shell pipe: `orchestrator | compressor | renderer`. The services share no code — only the contracts declared below.

