# bad Integration Chaos {#integration_chaos}

Real outages from our history. Never reintroduce any of these:

- camelCase or PascalCase field names in any JSON that crosses a service boundary.
- Logging to stdout — it corrupts the wire payload of the pipe.
- Letting a raw stack trace, panic, or uncaught exception escape to stdout instead of the shared error envelope.
- Regenerating or dropping `request_id` mid-pipeline — it breaks tracing across the three services.
- Adding a third-party dependency to any service. The whole pipeline runs on language standard libraries only.

# build {#pipeline_build}

- `scripts/build.sh` — builds all three services (must stay green after any change).
- `scripts/run_demo.sh [text]` — builds if needed, then runs the full pipeline end to end.

# read README.md

Before changing the pipeline topology — adding a service, reordering stages, or altering what flows between them — re-read the repository README and keep its architecture section true.

# notes

Spec-internal: this root baseline is deliberately the only place where the shared/*.hint contracts are included, so a contract change is a one-file edit. Folder hints below restate nothing — they only add language-local rules.
